eNCA's Faith Mangope speaks to Joburg's executive mayor Dr. Mpho Phalatse. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg will only cut off customers whose unpaid bills are not in dispute. Johannesburg Mayor Mpho Phalatse says she inherited a huge billing crisis when she took office. READ: Nelson Mandela Bay Metro ratepayers threaten legal action The city is on a mission to collect the R38-billion it's owed by residents, businesses and government.